00:38:10.976 --> 00:38:14.656
is not well-tolerated, my other clinicians might think, "Oh, it's not so bad."

625
00:38:15.456 --> 00:38:16.426
So there might be some

626
00:38:17.616 --> 00:38:18.676
subjectivity in that.

627
00:38:19.756 --> 00:38:23.066
The advantage is that then we can use the standard designs that we have been using.

628
00:38:23.276 --> 00:38:27.166
Right? There's plenty of designs that we currently use, and all of those designs

629
00:38:27.196 --> 00:38:31.006
can be used to recommend the

630
00:38:31.056 --> 00:38:31.336
dose.

631
00:38:33.236 --> 00:38:36.976
The second concept is incorporating PRO formally by setting a threshold.

632
00:38:37.036 --> 00:38:41.026
So what do I mean by that? So the DLT threshold that we have

633
00:38:41.076 --> 00:38:44.836
for CTCAE is 25%. If we figure out how to

634
00:38:44.856 --> 00:38:48.585
define tolerability from the patient perspective, we can set another

635
00:38:48.596 --> 00:38:52.476
threshold for that. So we can say that, for example, here, I don't want to see

636
00:38:52.536 --> 00:38:56.256
more than 35% of the patients saying that they have a severe

637
00:38:56.996 --> 00:38:59.645
adverse event or severe symptom that they cannot tolerate.

638
00:39:00.376 --> 00:39:04.145
In scenario one, assuming that we knew, this is hypothetical,

639
00:39:04.436 --> 00:39:08.136
the probability of toxicity at each dose level, here I have five dose

