00:39:24.936 --> 00:39:28.516
that would be well-tolerated. In scenario two, however,

646
00:39:30.436 --> 00:39:33.156
based on the clinician threshold, it would be dose level four.

647
00:39:33.376 --> 00:39:36.536
So this is where we have a concern, that if we use a threshold for

648
00:39:36.696 --> 00:39:40.436
35% from the patient perspective, the patients would say that

649
00:39:40.556 --> 00:39:41.436
anything

650
00:39:43.496 --> 00:39:47.416
above a dose level two would not be well-tolerated from their perspective.

651
00:39:47.956 --> 00:39:51.766
So it would be more a dose level two or lower that would be considered

