655
00:40:01.496 --> 00:40:03.256
which accounts for late onset toxicity.

656
00:40:04.316 --> 00:40:08.236
So the framework is as follow. You select the threshold that you think for

657
00:40:08.296 --> 00:40:12.196
the DLT, which can be your standard 25%, and at the same

658
00:40:12.236 --> 00:40:16.096
time, you can select a threshold for the PRO, which can be

659
00:40:16.236 --> 00:40:19.436
35%, 55%, whatever you think is

660
00:40:19.496 --> 00:40:23.476
acceptable threshold. Of course, the higher the threshold, the less you're

661
00:40:23.536 --> 00:40:25.486
using the PRO information. Right?

662
00:40:25.536 --> 00:40:27.776
Because that's not going to come in very often.

663
00:40:27.816 --> 00:40:31.726
Then you obtain data both from the PRO and the CTCAE

664
00:40:31.816 --> 00:40:33.996
concurrently when you're conducting the trial.

665
00:40:34.576 --> 00:40:38.336
And the concept is that you would estimate the doses based on the PRO

