00:40:46.436 --> 00:40:48.396
would select the smaller of the two doses.

669
00:40:48.856 --> 00:40:52.396
And by doing that, you're basically ensuring that it is tolerable both from the

670
00:40:52.436 --> 00:40:55.656
patient perspective and the clinician original outcome.

671
00:40:56.356 --> 00:41:00.136
And you repeat this process until you recommend the

672
00:41:00.176 --> 00:41:04.136
recommendation dose. And by doing that, the dose that you're selecting

673
00:41:04.156 --> 00:41:07.876
would satisfy both the DLT threshold from the patient perspective and the

674
00:41:07.896 --> 00:41:08.766
clinician perspective.

675
00:41:10.956 --> 00:41:14.556
There is a software already developed to run simulations for the PRO

